Request info for a gene symbol

Source: R/ensemble_lookup_gene_symbol.R
lookup_gene_symbols.Rd

Queries Ensembl REST API (build 38 or 37). Includes gene coordinates, description and biotype (e.g. whether protein coding or not).

Usage

lookup_gene_symbols(gene_symbols, build = "GRCh38")

Arguments

gene_symbols

A character vector of gene symbols e.g. "ESPN"

build

Either 'GRCh38' (default) or 'GRCh37'.

Value

A tibble.

Examples

 lookup_gene_symbols(c("ARMS2", "CFH"))
#> # A tibble: 2 × 16
#>   version description       source display_name  start logic_name strand db_type
#>     <int> <chr>             <chr>  <chr>         <int> <chr>       <int> <chr>  
#> 1       1 age-related macu… ensem… ARMS2        1.22e8 ensembl_h…      1 core   
#> 2      17 complement facto… ensem… CFH          1.97e8 ensembl_h…      1 core   
#> # ℹ 8 more variables: end <int>, biotype <chr>, species <chr>, id <chr>,
#> #   seq_region_name <chr>, canonical_transcript <chr>, assembly_name <chr>,
#> #   object_type <chr>
